	dprr:hasNoteText "(pont. max.). pp. 65-72" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8850> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8850" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 727" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8849> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8849" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 727" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7540> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7540" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 237, 224, 212, 209. Proconsul 211 (MRR 1.274). Note that when he was summoned to Rome because of Hannibal's march on Rome he received a special grant of imperium within the city, ut par cum consulibus imperium esset (Liv. 26.9.10).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1723> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1723" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Imperium prorogued as Proconsul in Bruttium (Liv. 27.35.13-14, 36.13, and 40.14), whence he was summoned to protect Lucania (27.42.17)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1719> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1719" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Livy omits the regular list of prorogations for this year with the exception of Q. Fulvius Flaccus." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1689> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1689" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Imperium prorogued at Capua (Liv. 27.22.4, cf. 25.6)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1640> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1640" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Leg. Agr. 2.90; Liv. 27.6; 29.15.2; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 46f., 120, 448f.; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; and on Fabius, Cic. Brut. 72; Elog., CIL 1\n     .1, p. 193- Inscr. Ital. 13.3.80; Plut. Fab. 19. The Consuls first dealt with formal duties, the levies, and the colonies who had refused to send their quotas of men (Liv. 27.7.7 and 12-13, 8.11-13, and 9-11). Fabius in southern Italy won Manduria and recaptured Tarentum, though he was almost caught by Hannibal at Metapontum (Liv. 27.12, 15-16, cf. 20.9, and 25.1-5; Plut. Fab. 21-23; Polyb. 10.1; Cic. De Or. 2.273 and 290; sen. 10-11; Brut. 72; Elogium; Strab. 6.3.1, 278 c; Val. Max. 7.3.7; Plin. NH 34.40; Sil. It. 15.320-333; Frontin. Str. 4.7.36; Plut. Cat. Mai. 2.3; Apophth. Fab. 4 and 6; Marc. 21 and 25; Polyaen. 8.14.3; App. Hann. 49; Eutrop. 3.16.1-2; Auct. Vir. Ill. 43.5-6; Augustin CD 1.6; Oros. 4.18.5; Zon. 9.8). Other towns surrendered to him (Eutrop. 3.16) and he returned to celebrate a triumph (Elogium; Plut. Fab. 23.1-2; Comp. Per. et Fab. 2; see Degrassi 551). Chosen Princeps Senatus (see below, Censors). Fulvius held the election of Censors (Liv. 27.11.7), went to Capua, and received the surrender of several towns of the Lucani and Hirpini (27.15.2-3), and returned to Rome to hold elections (27.21.1-5)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1617> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1617" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Imperium prorogued as Proconsul (Liv. 26.33.13; 27.3.1-5) for a year at Capua (Liv. 26.28.6 and 13). On his dealings with the Campanians, see Liv. 27.33-34; 27.3.1-7. See above, Dictator." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1597> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1597" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Appointed, after Valerius' refusal to do so, by Marcellus to hold the elections (Liv. 27.5.14-19, and 6.1-12; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 46f., 120, 448f.)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1566> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1566" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the discrepancies in the accounts of the actions of the military leaders during Hannibal's march on Rome, such that there is doubt if Fulvius Flaccus even left Campania, see De Sanctis, 3.2.302f., 336-340; CAH 8.80; Crake, 203." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1565> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1565" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Imperium prorogued as Proconsul for the siege of Capua (Liv. 25.41.13; 26.1.2, 8.9, and 9.10). Summoned from Capua to defend Rome\n     against Hannibal, he then returned and carried the siege through till the town capitulated (Polyb. 9.3-7, and 9; Liv. 26.4-16; 28.41.13; App. Hann. 38-43; Zon. 9.6; cf. Vell. 2.8.3; Val. Max. 2.3.3; 2.8.4; 3.2, ext. 1, 8.1; 5.2.1; Frontin. Str. 4.7.29; Sil. It. 11.114f.; 12.570-752; Plut. Comp. Per. et Fab. 2.1; Flor. 1.22.43; Oros. 4.17.4 and 12)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1513> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1513" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 25.2.4, and 3.1; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 46f., 119, 446f., cf. Fast. Fer. Lat., Degrassi 148f.; Val. Max. 2.4.7; Frontin. Str. 4.1.44; Fest. 438 L; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod. Both Consuls cooperated in Campania, in the capture of Hanno's camp at Beneventum, and in reducing Capua (Liv. 25.3.3; 25.7-9, 12-15, 18-20, and 22; App. Hann. 37; cf. Sil. It. 12.479-506). Fulvius remained in charge at Capua while Claudius held the elections in Rome (Liv. 25.41.8-13). See below, Pontifices, on Fulvius." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1475> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1475" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See above, Dictator." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1447> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1447" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Was assigned his jurisdiction and command of the city extra sortem (Liv. 24.9.5; see Mommsen, Str. 2.209, note 2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1444> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1444" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Election Liv. 24.9.4." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1414> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1414" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Set up a tribunal near the Piscina publica (Liv. 23.32.4). Received command of ships to protect the seacoast near the city (Liv. 23.32.15 and 18). Arranged for the defense of Sardinia (Liv. 23.34.11-17), and for supplies needed by the Spanish army (Liv. 23.48.4-49.5). Received captives of war from Sardinia (Liv. 23.41.7).{255}" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1412> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1412" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Election Liv. 23.24.4 Provinces Liv. 23.30.18." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1400> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1400" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Q. Fulvius Flaccus succeeded Q. Aelius Paetus. On Paetus, see Liv. 22.35.2. Flaccus competed unsuccessfully for election as Pont. Max. in 212 (25.5.2-4), and died after 205 (28.45.2-7)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1399> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1399" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 23.21.7." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1352> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1352" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Brought Servilius' army to the Dictator Fabius (Liv. 22.12.1)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1351> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1351" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The praenomen Quintus depends on Münzer's identification of this Fulvius with the Consul of 237, 224, 212, and 209." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1256> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1256" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Polyb. 2.31.8; Fast. Cap. (names entire); Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Oros. 4.13.11; Cassiod.; cf. on Manlius, Liv. 23.34.15; Degrassi 44f., 118, 440f. These Consuls forced the Boii to submit, and were the first Roman commanders to cross the Po and battle the Insubres (Polyb. 2.31.8-10; Oros. 4.3.11; cf. Liv. Per. 20; Zon. 8.20)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1233> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1233" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Abdicated because of a flaw in their election (Fast. Cap., Degrassi 44f., 117, 440f.; cf. on Fulvius, Liv. 23.30.18; 25.5.3; 28.45.2; on Manlius, 23.34.15; 25.5.3; 27.11.10)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1212> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1212" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Eutrop. 3.2; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd., and Chr. Pasc. (with Caudinus, the only name reported, corrupted to Claudius); Cassiod.; Zon. 9.18; see Degrassi 44f., 117, 438f. Both campaigned against Gauls and Ligurians (Polyb. 2.21.3-6; Flor. 1.19.5; Eutrop. 3.2; Zon. 8.18)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertion/9879> rdfs:label "Post Assertion: #9879" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertion ;
